# gen212+gen214 (OUTPUT side): the agent's reply phrasings are KB knowledge
# (response_template/2 in kb/core/responses.p0), filled by kb_response, and the class
# GROWS at runtime. A new greeting wording is taught through the SAME generic teach path
# (try_teach_form + learnable/3, mode=fill) — "use \"…\" to greet a new name" — and the
# next name learned is welcomed with it. kb_response rotates over the phrasings, so the
# base and taught forms alternate (the gen55 anti-repeat instinct).
> my name is Ada
< Nice to meet you, Ada!
> use "Welcome, {name}!" to greet a new name
< Got it - I'll take "Welcome, {name}!" as a way to greet a new name now.
> my name is Bob
< Welcome, Bob!
